originalText.text:
Dr. Chanchani (and the entire medical staff at NYU) were superb. While this is a group practice, the staff was v. helpful with scheduling me around Dr. Chanchani's calendar.

Towards the tail end of the visits, the front desk staff helped/encouraged me scheduled with other doctors in case Dr. Chanchani is not scheduled for the night of my delivery ...

Welp, the front staff was correct. Dr. Chanchani was not on scheduled that evening and Dr. Aquino (who is equally stellar)- delivered our little one without c-section interference (even though I had day of preeclampsia).

The morning right after delivery, Dr. Chanchani made her way over to visit and check in on my physically and mentally. I am so thankful for her and the entire staff at NYU!
